  <div class="ct">
  
<blockquote>Other students, who don't know the material beforehand, expect to be 'taught' the information and skills they don't have, and demoralized grad students and TA's aren't that helpful while the course teacher is off somewhere.</blockquote>
This seems to read as a complaint that students starting a class haven't already mastered the material taught in the class. Or, even more bluntly, it's a complaint that if most students took the final on the first day of class, they'd flunk. If that's the case, what's the point of having classes in the first place? Why not just have tests?<br />

